http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br><br>Needless to say, I'm getting more than a little sick of it.  It seems that the EQ techs don't seem to give a damn.  I wouldn't mind, being one case, except for the fact that problems with machines that closely match my own configuration are positively rife!<br><br>I'm really pissed off, EVERYTHING but EQ works perfectly.<br><br>/mild rant <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crime Lord</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 8:16:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> Music has always been stuttery for me, too. I just turn it off and use SneakyAmp. SneakyAmp is a plug in for WinAmp that monitors your keyboard controls. Just run WinAmp with SneakyAmp on, and type something like winamp play airplane &quot;&quot; if you want to hear a song by Jefferson Airplane, or so on.<br><br>As for your grainy graphics, fool around in your options settings. Check to see if your normal video card is selected, and so on. <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>Agent of The Ring <BR>"I thought I saw my own worst enemy, a kind of demon. And it was me."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 8:26:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> The music isn't a problem, I can just about deal with the music.  It's the infernal crashing that's causing me a headache. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vardalis>Vardalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 10:25:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> When EQ is disconnected on my machine, for whatever reason, it usually takes out my network, forcing me to reinstall it, adds new sound driver entries which don't point to any hardware in my computer, and generally buggers it up. I have taken to cancelling my account every month just in case I can't get EQ to run after one of these fiascos.   If Verant had a toll-free number I'd be ranting and screaming at them.<br><br>I always manage to fix it, so far, anyways.  You may have to reinstall your video and sound drivers, run Scandisk, etc.etc. etc.<br>Formatting your HD is pretty drastic. You'll have to reinstall any driver software not included in Windows, like your video and sound drivers, perhaps, and any other software that adds or messes with entries in the registry. <p>Vardalis, Human Magician<br>Have pet, will travel.<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 10:46:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> Well, I had to format my drive.  Somehow, it had corrupted every single driver I had and wrecked half my hard drive (luckily I have dual hard drives and I kept most of my important stuff on the second one).  I was getting Windows protection errors every time I started my machine that would cause it to bomb out in everything apart from the command line prompt.  And as much as EQ is primitive compared to some games, I don't think even EQ can run in DOS... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 10:59:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hmm</span><hr size=1> weird... doublecheck all your drivers and good luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>*has a pretty good experience lately.. no more crashes, and none of the funny &quot;keyboard sticky&quot; issue either*<br><br> <p><center><i><a href=mailto:kyrial_moonlight@lycos.com>Kyrial Moonli