comes up wanting to install drivers, tell it no. Just deal with the 16 color defaults for now.<br><br>Then install DX8.1 before installing ANYTHING else. (Well, you can install your network drivers first, just so you can grab the DX installer from Microsoft. That's pretty safe and worked for me.) Let it do all of its updating and rebooting and whatever. THEN install your video drivers, and sound drivers, and whatever else.<br><br>The DX installer apparently has a bad habit of corrupting pre-existing drivers without saying anything. I could do a clean format, install video and sound, then do DX last, and EQ would crash like crazy. Formatted again, installed DX first, and now it runs fine.<br><br>Of course I have no idea what kind of system you're running so this may end up being completely useless to you, but at least it could be something to try. Also try switching from 16bit resoultion to 32bit in your eqclient.ini (I think) file. A patch a while back completely broke 16bit compatibility for me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaileena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaileena</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 1:46:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dabros.com/images/animebabejen/newkai.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> I've had all of the perviously mentioned problems and more.<br><br>And then there's the fact that they're raising the price of the game. If they raise the price, I for one, would like to see that most, if not all, of these problems are fixed. I know I don't wanna be paying $13 for crap.<br><br>They better be usuing that money to buy better crew for fixing our problems. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>*Kai* <p><img src="http://www.dabros.com/images/animebabejen/kaikai.jpg"> <br><i> ~ "...Because everything happens for a reason" ~ <a href="http://www.geocities.com/animebabejen/Kaileena.html"> <font color="FFFFFF"> Kaileena </a></i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uermok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ermok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 2:17:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/lethron/hfv.jpg height=137 width=77></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> I recommend a clean format.  Changing drivers and trying to upgrade your computer without one is like comparing a sponge bath to a good shower. <p><p align="center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/lethron/ermoksig1.gif"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vardalis>Vardalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 4:28:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> I'd like to believe that Verant will use the extra money to provide better support.  Unfortunately, I don't.  What will happen, IMHO:<br><br>1 - Verant will raise the monthly fee.  No one will cancel their account because of it.<br><br>2- Customer service will get slightly better, but still suck.  No one will cancel their account because of it.<br><br>3- All of us will bitch, moan and complain, and spend hours repairing the mess EQ causes from time to time on our computers.  No one will cancel their account because of it.<br><br>4 - If another MMORPG comes along that is more fun than EQ, and at least as stable, all of the above is moot, since we, and a lot of others, will drop EQ like a hot rock.<br> <p>Vardalis, Human Magician<br>Have pet, will travel.<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/29/02 7:07:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Collapses, exhausted*</span><hr size=1> It's working..  Sort of.  I've given up on the sound, but enabling DMA on both hard drives seems to have sped the game up enough that any instabilities just come and go.  Other than that though..  Kuso... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=484.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=484.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% b